io.github.struppigel.parser.sections.idata

Class LookupTableEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.struppigel.parser.sections.idata.LookupTableEntry
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    NameEntry, NullEntry, OrdinalEntry

    public abstract class LookupTableEntry
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a lookup table entry. Every lookup table entry is either an ordinal entry, a name entry or a null entry. The null entry indicates the end of the lookup table.

        Creates a lookup table entry based on the given import table bytes, the size of the entry, the offset of the entry and the virtual address of the import section

        Parameters:
        mmbytes - memory mapped PE
        entryRVA - address to the lookuptable entry relative to iltRVA
        entrySize - the size of one entry
        virtualAddress - the address to the import section
        iltRVA - address to the last ILT or the IAT
        dirEntry - the directory entry
        fileOffset - the file offset to the lookup table entry to create
        loadInfo - (undocumented)
        iltVA - (undocumented)

        lookup table entry
